<TITLE> Price cut will follow sound supply chain: Faruque </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gopalganj, Jan 10 (bdnews24.com)  Essential commodities will be brought within people's reach by smoothening the supply chain, the commerce minister has said. "Transport fares will come down if the price of diesel reduces. The prices of commodities will also be controlled," Faruque Khan told reporters during a visit to his hometown Gopalganj's municipality market on Saturday "Prices of commodities started falling as soon as Awami League-led grand alliance formed government," he added. Prices of rice, lentil, and edible oil along with other commodities are becoming affordable, he obsered Earlier, the minister exchanged views with leaders of Gopalganj Chambers of Commerce and Industries at the circuit house. He asked the business leaders to expand activities of the chamber. He also joined another views-exchange meeting with leaders and activists of his electoral areasKashiani and Moshudpur Upazila. The minister, on behalf of prime minister Sheikh Hasina, laid floral wreaths at independence hero Sheikh Mujibur Rahman's mausoleum in Tungipara the anniversary of his homecoming day. bdnews2
